Patch 0077 — addresses user's question: "you missed the AI compute
bottleneck early — who called it first, why did we miss it?"

ROOT CAUSE
SemiAnalysis (Dylan Patel) called HBM3E + CoWoS shortage 6+ months
before Tier-1 media. We weren't even pulling SemiAnalysis. AND when
specialist sources DID appear (TrendForce, Power Engineering), our
SignalQualityTier classifier downgraded them to D_SPECULATIVE because
they aren't Reuters / Bloomberg.

FIX
1. Added SemiAnalysis + Digitimes RSS feeds (the two most important
   early-callers we were missing).
2. New module lib/news/early-callers.ts — curated registry of 18
   domain-specialist sources mapped to SystemNode domains they have
   track records in:
     SemiAnalysis    → COMPUTE/MEMORY/PACKAGING/FAB/INTERCONNECT (95)
     Digitimes       → PACKAGING/FAB/COMPUTE/MEMORY (90)
     TrendForce      → MEMORY/COMPUTE/PACKAGING (88)
     Power Eng       → ENERGY/NUCLEAR/RENEWABLE (85)
     World Nuclear   → NUCLEAR/RESOURCE_SCARCITY (88)
     Defense News    → DEFENSE/AEROSPACE (82)
     Datacenter Dyn  → COMPUTE/ENERGY/COOLING (80)
     ServeTheHome    → COMPUTE/INTERCONNECT/COOLING (76)
     ICIS / S&P CI   → RESOURCE_SCARCITY/OIL_GAS (75-80)
     Steelmint       → RESOURCE_SCARCITY/MFG (78)
     Livefist / IDRW → DEFENSE/AEROSPACE India (80)
     ET Infra/Telecom→ ENERGY/TELECOM India (72-75)
     etc.
3. New SignalQualityTier value: EC_EARLY_CALLER. Promoted ABOVE
   C_INDUSTRY when source has domain match with article's SystemNode.
   SemiAnalysis on COMPUTE_INFRA → EC (B-equivalent).
   SemiAnalysis on NUCLEAR_INFRA → C (off-domain, no promotion).
4. classifySignalQuality now accepts primary_node + nodes_hit. Wired
   into route.ts to pass graph node info.

This means HBM/CoWoS/grid/HALEU/defence early signals from specialist
sources now flow through with full institutional weight instead of
being silenced as "speculative."
